meanings.definition: To keep away or not be affected by.
examples: If I try hard, I can resist eating the chocolate cake.

images.alt: Photo of person holding her hand out with palm facing the viewer.
images.description: Photo of person holding her hand out with palm facing the viewer. She is using this gesture to say 'no.'
images.caption: Her gesture shows that this woman is saying no, or resisting.

source.title: Portrait Photo of Woman in Red Top Wearing Black Framed Eyeglasses Holding Out Her Hand in Stop Gesture
source.author: Andrea Piacquadio

examples: He has a good outlook on life, and that has helped him move forward.
The coach said positive things about how the team was playing.

images.alt: Photo of a hand with thumb pointing up.
images.description: A hand with its thumb pointing up.
images.caption: Thumbs up is a positive sign!

examples: The twins look alike but have made different choices for what they want to do in life.

images.alt: Photo of two people next to each other.
images.description: Two people who look alike, but who have different expressions and are wearing different clothes.
images.caption: Twins look alike, but they can have different personalities and interests, too.

source.title: Photo Of Woman Beside Each Other
source.author: Marlon Alves

meanings.definition: To be present at; to go to.
examples: I plan to attend college when I get older.

images.alt: Photo of a person reading a book.
images.description: Photo of a person reading a book. He is next to a bookshelf filled with books.
images.caption: When you attend school, you can go to the library for books or to use computers.

source.title: Concentrated black man reading book in library
source.author: Cem Saka
